00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:57,820
最终我们不得不从莉莉的房间逃离 她有个老鼠室友
Okay, we have to get Lily out of that apartment. Her roommate is a raccoon.

44
00:01:57,830 --> 00:02:01,100
我想让她来我那住 可是我有只狗 她对狗毛过敏
I'd offer her my place, but I've got dogs and she's allergic.

45
00:02:01,110 --> 00:02:04,440
狗?  我跟她前男友住一起 她对那个估计更敏感
Dogs? I live with her ex-boyfriend. I think she's a little more allergic to that.

46
00:02:04,450 --> 00:02:06,970
你那可以吗?巴尼 我知道你那里很神秘
What about your place, Barney? I know it's shrouded in mystery,

47
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:08,160
但肯定会有个沙发
but it's gotta have a couch.

48
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:10,480
想住巴尼超人的城堡？没门! (他把fortress of solitude 改称fortress of barnitude  把自己比作超人)
The Fortress of Barnitude? No way.

49
00:02:10,490 --> 00:02:11,910
别这样 她很惨啊
Come on. She's desperate.

50
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:14,040
我对我要带回去的女人是有条件的
Hmm, normally a prerequisite for the women I bring home,

51
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:15,620
但是 她不予考虑
but... pass.

52
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:20,010
你们当中的一个人非常非常走运
One of you guys is very, very lucky because I have...

53
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:23,480
因为有张多的艾拉妮丝・莫莉塞特演唱会的票 谁想去?
a boom, an extra ticket to the Alanis Morissette concert. Who's in?

54
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:24,970
- 很明显 没有 - 不
- Absolutely not. - No.

55
00:02:24,980 --> 00:02:27,940
见鬼! 大概一个月前我就搞到票了 当时想和莉莉一起去
Damn! I got these tickets, like, months ago for me and Lily

56
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:30,300
现在想找个伴都找不到
and now I can't find anyone to go with me.

57
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:32,280
所以很怀念以前成双入对的日子
This is what I miss about being in a couple.

58
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:34,250
这样总有人可以陪我去演唱会
I always had someone to go to concerts with,

59
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:35,840
去菜市场
or farmer's market,

60
00:02:35,850 --> 00:02:37,430
还有早午餐
or brunch.

61
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,070
上帝  我上午没有吃饭
God, I miss brunch!

62
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:42,060
这样的话我认为你可以自己吃早午餐
Well, I guess you could-- well, you could try going to brunch alone.

63
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:44,170
你认为我没有试过?
Oh, you don't think I've tried?

64
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:45,850
一位
Table for one.

65
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:48,160
一对?
One couple?

66
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:49,530
不 就我一个人
Um, no, just me.

67
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:50,930
真的?
Really?

68
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:52,730
一个人的早午餐?
For brunch?

69
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:54,880
对 我不是开玩笑
You're right. Who am I kidding?

70
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:59,250
波普餐厅 真是个好地方 明天我们去吃早午餐吧
Ooh, The Popover Pantry. That place is great. Can we go get brunch tomorrow?

71
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:00,640
可以啊 亲爱的
Of course, sweetie.

72
00:03:00,650 --> 00:03:01,850
我能跟你们一起去吗?
Can I go with you guys?

73
00:03:01,860 --> 00:03:04,480
确定?跟我们去吃早午饭?
Really? For brunch?

74
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:07,130
上帝!我讨厌单身!
God, I hate being single!

75
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:12,350
好吧 我赌匹兹堡赢
Okay, I'll take the over on the Pittsburgh game.

76
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,580
匹兹堡对西雅图　两个星期以来
Oh, and P. to the S., I never got my payout

77
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:16,640
我就没在西雅图上面赢过钱
from Seattle from two weeks ago.

78
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:20,860
好的  不要逼我向赌博委员会投诉你
Yeah. Don't make me call the gaming commission on you.

79
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:23,970
我肯定他们会对这很感兴趣
I'm sure they'd be very interested to know what's going on over there.

80
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:26,680
好吗?明白吗?
All right? All right?

81
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:29,600
我也爱你 妈妈 多保重
Okay, I love you, too, Mom. Take care.

82
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:35,020
莉莉! 你好
Hello,  Lily.

83
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:40,320
你成功的获取了我的机密
You've somehow managed to circumvent my security.

84
00:03:40,330 --> 00:03:42,170
你怎么做到的
How did you do it?

85
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,900
泰德把备用钥匙给我了
Ted gave me your spare key.

86
00:03:43,910 --> 00:03:46,010
备用钥匙! 太聪明了!
Spare key, brilliant!

87
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:48,200
我很不好意思 不过我也就只能来这了
I'm sorry, but you know I'd only come here

88
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:50,280
我没别地儿可去了
if I had no other choice.

89
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:54,040
今晚  我正准备早点睡觉的时候
But earlier today, I was getting ready to go to sleep and...

90
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:08,210
你好 （立陶宛语）
Sveikas.

91
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:13,340
太糟了
That's terrible.

92
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:15,050
好吧 改天见
Well, see ya.

93
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:17,270
晕 我今晚不能留下吗?
Well, can I stay here maybe?

94
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:20,760
我很愿意 但是房间不够
Oh... I'd let you, but I don't have any room.

95
00:04:20,770 --> 00:04:22,840
但是你住的是两室的房间啊
You live in a two-bedroom apartment.

96
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:25,670
你用一间屋子专门放衣服
You have one room just for your suits.

97
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:29,680
在我生命里 我的衣服也是家庭成员
Hey, I'm at a point in my life where my suits are my family.

98
00:04:29,690 --> 00:04:31,740
莉莉 看看周围
Look around you, Lily.

99
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:34,370
你现在置身于 一个单身汉的国度
You are in the heart of bachelor country,

100
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:37,700
作为一个女人 你在我这里是不受欢迎的
and as a woman, you are an illegal immigrant here.

101
00:04:37,710 --> 00:04:41,740
现在你可以申请一张只有 12小时的"性"签证
Now, you can try to apply for a sex visa, but that only lasts 12 hours.

102
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:44,890
如果你床上功夫好的话 还有长达14小时的多次往返签证
14 if you qualify for multiple entry.

103
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:49,920
要是单纯的小女生肯定说 "不会吧"
Eww... is something some lame, judgmental chick would say,

104
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:53,730
但是我要得到多次往返签证 来　击掌
but I say give me multiple high fives.

105
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:56,180
哇　你真是不顾一切
Wow, you really are desperate.

106
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:57,370
那确实
I really am.

107
00:04:57,380 --> 00:05:01,300
好吧 你可以待两天
Okay, you can stay here for two days.

108
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:05,320
只有一条你要遵守 不能乱动我的东西
But I only have one rule. You can't change anything.

109
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:08,490
我没有理由乱动你的东西 这里真是...
Why would I change anything? This place is...

110
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:10,530
...完美
...perfect.

111
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:13,850
除了你没有电视这个事实
Except for the fact that you don't have a TV.

112
00:05:13,860 --> 00:05:15,900
看见那面墙了吗?
See that wall?

113
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:22,540
300寸的液晶电视
300-inch flat-screen.

114
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:25,460
只有东京有卖的 但是我有个熟人
They only sell them in Japan, but I know a guy.

115
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:29,270
用了一艘可以装下金刚的船 才把它弄回来的
Had to ship it over in a tugboat like freakin' King Kong.

116
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,730
亮的晃眼睛
It hurts my eyes.

117
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:33,670
是啊 这光无法关掉
Yeah. That doesn't go away.

118
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:37,080
- 嘿 - 嘿 你去哪了?
- Hey. - Hey, where have you been?

119
00:05:37,090 --> 00:05:38,810
艾拉妮丝・莫莉塞特的演唱会
The Alanis Morissette concert.

120
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:39,890
一个人?
By yourself?

121
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:42,210
事实上我是和一个法学院的朋友去的
No, actually I went with a friend from law school.

122
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:45,570
真的?她是谁啊?
Oh, really? Who's this friend?

123
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:47,350
布莱德
Brad.

124
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:51,640
- 兄弟  艾拉妮丝・莫莉塞特摇滚? - 完全正确
- Bro, Alanis Morissette rocks! - Totally!

125
00:05:51,650 --> 00:05:53,370
不可思议吧 我今晚差点就不能来了
I can't believe I almost didn't come tonight.

126
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,170
我猜  这两张票是你打算和莉莉一起去的
Let me guess: You bought the tickets for you and Lily

127
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,680
在她甩了你之前
right before she dumped you.

128
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,550
是啊 你怎么知道的
Yeah, how'd you know?

129
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,340
我也才被甩了
I just got dumped myself.

130
00:06:00,350 --> 00:06:03,030
什么?卡洛跟你分手了?
What, Kara broke up with you?

131
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:06,120
很遗憾 这太郁闷了
I'm sorry, man. That sucks.

132
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:11,020
布莱德你喜欢早午饭吗?
Brad, do you like brunch?

133
00:06:11,030 --> 00:06:12,630
你请他吃早午饭?
You invited him to brunch?

134
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,060
是啊 我请了 有问题?
Yeah, I invited him to brunch. Why, is that weird?

135
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:18,940
是的 问题就在于 你邀请他一起吃早午饭
Yes. That's why I was all, "You invited him to brunch?"

136
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:22,560
为什么朋友就不能去吃呢?
Why can't two guys who are friends go to brunch?

137
00:06:22,570 --> 00:06:25,050
因为这个有点
Because brunch is kind of...

138
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:26,490
娘娘腔
G irly.

139
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,980
娘娘腔?早餐不娘娘腔
Girly? Breakfast isn't girly.

140
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:31,480
午饭不娘娘腔 偏偏早午餐有?
Lunch isn't girly. What makes brunch girly?

141
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:32,440
我不知道
I don't know.

142
00:06:32,450 --> 00:06:34,310
比如说马听起来娘娘腔
There's nothing girly about a horse.

143
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,130
角也没有
Nothing girly about a horn,

144
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:38,830
但是独角兽听说来就娘娘腔
but put them together and you get a unicorn.

145
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,220
管你们怎么说
I don't care what either of you say,

146
00:06:41,230 --> 00:06:44,540
我要和布莱德去波普餐厅
I am going to The Popover Pantry with Brad.

147
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,330
我们去了 我们饿了
We're here. We're hungry.

148
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:48,770
习惯早午餐吧
Get used to it, brunch.

149
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:57,160
-闻起来真香 - 谢谢夸奖
- Hmm... smells delicious. - Thank you.

150
00:06:57,170 --> 00:06:59,820
冰箱里没有吃的了 所以我买了点
There was no food in the fridge, so I picked up...

151
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,510
你在做什么?
What are you doing?

152
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,430
莉莉 再重复一遍规矩
Lily, what was the first rule again?

153
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,690
不要乱动任何东西!
Don't change anything.

154
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,470
那第二条是什么?
And what was the second rule?

155
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,260
-规则二 没有规则二? - 是的!
- There was no second rule. - Exactly!

156
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:11,390
这里只有一条规则 而你破了规矩
There was only one rule and you broke it.

157
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:14,740
我买食物 这个也算?
I bought groceries. That counts as changing something?

158
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,950
莉莉 如果我想要冰箱 里放满了食物
Lily, if I wanted a fridge full of groceries,

159
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,920
或者早上有新鲜的咖啡
or fresh coffee in the morning,

